reviewText: Ordered as a gift.  Never heard anything about it.
I love John Wayne! but this item is an insult to him and his fans! poor quality! stay away!

This 3-set dvd has some great material in it - interviews with John Ford and Wayne, a documentary with James Stewart, Henry Fonda, and John Ford, a Lucy show featuring Wayne, etc.  However, some of the material - particularly the Art Linkletter show (of which Wayne appears only for a few seconds at most) and the Wild West show featuring John Ford, Gene Autry, and others had extremely poor quality.  I would have preferred to pay more for the set to have restored footage.  As it is, I have watched it and will put it in the Goodwill pile instead of adding it to my collection due to the poor quality of some of the items.
I'm a John Wayne fan - I collect various such memorabilia.  It is a good little DVD if you're into John Wayne.
Everything you need to know and more!!
